title: Untitled
Fastest way to create many files
content:
time for i in {110000..120000..64} ; do z=$(($i+64)); seq $i $z | parallel -j 64 touch file{}.txt; done

# 64 seconds

time for i in {120000..130000}; do echo this > file$1.txt; done

title: PiNas status
content:
echo "===== PiNAS STATUS =====" && \
echo && \
echo "--- RAID ---" && cat /proc/mdstat && \
echo && \
echo "--- Disks ---" && lsblk && \
echo && \
echo "--- Space ---" && df -h | grep -E "raid|Filesystem" && \
echo && \
echo "--- Temps ---" && \
vcgencmd measure_temp 2>/dev/null || echo "CPU temp tool not available" && \
for d in /dev/sd[a-d]; do sudo smartctl -A $d 2>/dev/null | grep -E "Temperature|194"; done && \
echo && \
echo "--- Network ---" && ip a | grep -E "eth0|wlan0|inet "
